                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 4.964,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 48630,
                                "text": "On Iowa versus Tovar will be announced by Justice Ginsburg."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 4.964,
                        "stop": 357.973,
                        "byte_start": 48630,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 4.964,
                                "stop": 14.439,
                                "byte_start": 48630,
                                "byte_stop": 86455,
                                "text": "The Sixth Amendment secures the criminal defendants who face incarceration the right to counsel at all stages of the criminal process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.439,
                                "stop": 19.874,
                                "byte_start": 86455,
                                "byte_stop": 108189,
                                "text": "That right includes counsel\u0027s aid prior to entering a guilty plea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.874,
                                "stop": 51.797,
                                "byte_start": 108189,
                                "byte_stop": 235875,
                                "text": "The Iowa Supreme Court in the case before us held that the Sixth Amendment requires the Trial Court to give defendants who seek to plead guilty unaided by counsel two specific admonitions: first, that foregoing the aid of counsel entails the risk that a tenable defense will be overlooked, and second, that an uncounseled defendant loses the opportunity to gain an independent opinion on whether it is wise to plead guilty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.797,
                                "stop": 57.372,
                                "byte_start": 235875,
                                "byte_stop": 258236,
                                "text": "We hold that neither warning is mandated by the Sixth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.372,
                                "stop": 74.789,
                                "byte_start": 258236,
                                "byte_stop": 327931,
                                "text": "The constitutional requirement is satisfied when the Trial Court informs the accused of the nature of the charges against him of his right to be counseled regarding his plea and of the range of allowable punishments attendant upon the entry of a guilty plea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.789,
                                "stop": 95.064,
                                "byte_start": 327931,
                                "byte_stop": 409015,
                                "text": "The defendant respondent, Felipe Edgardo Tovar, was charged in 1996, again in 1998, and for a third time in 2000 with driving under the influence of alcohol in Iowa Code OWI, operating while intoxicated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.064,
                                "stop": 102.001,
                                "byte_start": 409015,
                                "byte_stop": 436705,
                                "text": "He pled guilty in 1996 without counsel and again in 1998 with counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.001,
                                "stop": 110.367,
                                "byte_start": 436705,
                                "byte_stop": 470141,
                                "text": "In 2000, as a third-time offender, his punishment could be enhanced from an aggravated misdemeanor to a felony."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.367,
                                "stop": 122.615,
                                "byte_start": 470141,
                                "byte_stop": 519147,
                                "text": "To avoid that enhancement, Tovar through counsel asked the court not to account his first conviction because it was unattended by adequate information on his right to counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.615,
                                "stop": 135.565,
                                "byte_start": 519147,
                                "byte_stop": 570974,
                                "text": "At that 1996 first OWI plea hearing, Tovar informed the court as he earlier did in an initial appearance that he wished to plea guilty and to proceed without consel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.565,
                                "stop": 147.848,
                                "byte_start": 570974,
                                "byte_stop": 620084,
                                "text": "Inquiring into the voluntariness of Tovar\u2019s plea, the court told Tovar that if he elected to go to trial, he would be entitled to a jury, to counsel\u0027s assistance, and to other trial rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.848,
                                "stop": 155.534,
                                "byte_start": 620084,
                                "byte_stop": 650909,
                                "text": "The court further informed Tovar of the maximum and minimum penalties for a first OWI conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.534,
                                "stop": 172.488,
                                "byte_start": 650909,
                                "byte_stop": 718723,
                                "text": "Next, the court explained that before accepting Tovar\u2019s plea, the courts had to assure that Tovar was in fact guilty of the two elements of the charge: first, operating motor vehicle in Iowa, second, doing do while intoxicated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.488,
                                "stop": 184.022,
                                "byte_start": 718723,
                                "byte_stop": 764803,
                                "text": "Tovar confirmed that he was driving in Iowa and that an intoxilyzer test revealed a blood alcohol level that exceeded the legal limit twice over."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.022,
                                "stop": 193.454,
                                "byte_start": 764803,
                                "byte_stop": 802523,
                                "text": "The court then accepted Tovar\u2019s guilty plea and the next month sentenced him to the minimum term of two days in jail and a fine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.454,
                                "stop": 208.06,
                                "byte_start": 802523,
                                "byte_stop": 860933,
                                "text": "The Iowa Supreme Court reviewing Tovar\u2019s third OWI conviction held that because he was not given the two specific warnings just mentioned his first conviction could not be used to increase his third sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.06,
                                "stop": 210.317,
                                "byte_start": 860933,
                                "byte_stop": 870024,
                                "text": "We reverse that determination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.317,
                                "stop": 223.948,
                                "byte_start": 870024,
                                "byte_stop": 924568,
                                "text": "A waiver of counsel must be voluntary and intelligent but we have not prescribed any formula or script to be read to a defendant who states that he elects to plea guilty without counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 223.948,
                                "stop": 244.903,
                                "byte_start": 924568,
                                "byte_stop": 1008368,
                                "text": "The information the defendant must have to make an intelligent election between counsel and self-representation, our decisions indicate, will depend on a range of case specific factors including the defendant\u2019s educational sophistication, the complex or easily grasp nature of the charge and the stage of the proceeding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 244.903,
                                "stop": 258.091,
                                "byte_start": 1008368,
                                "byte_stop": 1061136,
                                "text": "In prescribing scripted admonitions and holding them necessary in every guilty plea instance, the Iowa Supreme Court overlooked this Court\u2019s guiding decisions which described a pragmatic approach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 258.091,
                                "stop": 282.294,
                                "byte_start": 1061136,
                                "byte_stop": 1157893,
                                "text": "Less formal warnings generally suffice pretrial, we have observed, because at that stage, the dangers and disadvantages of self-representation are less substantial when they are at trial where a defendant must cope with rules of procedure and evidence, the subtleties of jury selection, witness examination and cross-examination, objections to prosecutor\u0027s questions, and much more."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 282.294,
                                "stop": 309.889,
                                "byte_start": 1157893,
                                "byte_stop": 1268234,
                                "text": "Tovar, who bears the burden of proof that his guilty plea was inadequately informed, has never stated just what additional information counsel could have provided given the simplicity of the OWI charge he faced, nor has Tovar ever asserted that he was in fact unaware of his rights to counseled at the plea stage or that he did not understand the nature of the charge or the range of possible punishment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 309.889,
                                "stop": 321.627,
                                "byte_start": 1268234,
                                "byte_stop": 1315255,
                                "text": "The specific admonitions the Iowa Supreme Court mandated moreover might cause a defendant to wonder whether the court thinks he has a good defense, when in reality he does not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 321.627,
                                "stop": 330.44,
                                "byte_start": 1315255,
                                "byte_stop": 1350468,
                                "text": "We note finally that stage of free to adopt any guidelines to the acceptance of an uncounceled plea they deemed useful."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 330.44,
                                "stop": 339.237,
                                "byte_start": 1350468,
                                "byte_stop": 1385681,
                                "text": "We hold only that the two specific admonitions the Iowa Supreme Court ordered are not commanded by the Federal Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 339.237,
                                "stop": 357.973,
                                "byte_start": 1385681,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court\u2019s opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
